課程教材 Course Material
	    PowerPoint slides and suggested textbooks    

參考書目 References
	    (1) Integrated Optics, Theory and Technology, 6th Edition, Robert G. Hunsperger (Springer, 2009)
(2) Fundamentals of Optoelectronics, C. R. Pollack (Irwin, 1995)
(3) Optoelectronics and Photonics: Principles and Practices, S. O. Kasap (Prentice-Hall, 2001)
(4) Optical Electronics in Modern Communications, 5th Edition, A. Yariv (Oxford University Press, 1997)
(5) Fundamentals of Optical Waveguides, 2nd Edition, K. Okamoto (Academic Press, 2006)    

備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
        無    

核心能力 Competence
■ 具微電子工程相關領域之專業知識。
 To possess professional knowledge in the field of microelectronic engineering
□ 策劃及執行專題研究之能力。
 The ability to plan and carry out a research project.
■ 撰寫專業論文之能力。
 To write a professional-quality dissertation.
■ 創新思考及獨立解決問題之能力。
 Innovative thinking and the ability to solve problems independently.
■ 跨領域人員協調整合之能力。
 Multidisciplinary coordination and integration capabilities.
□ 良好的國際觀以及理解專業倫理與社會責任之能力。
 A solid international outlook and the ability to understand professional ethics and social responsibility.
□ 領導、管理及規劃之能力。
 Leadership, management and planning abilities.
□ 終身自我學習成長之能力。
 The ability to learn and develop throughout life.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       1 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The students will learn to apply the basic concepts of integrated optics to the designs of various active and passive integarted photonic devices.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction and discussion of syllabus2Review of integrated optics (I)3Review of integarted optics (II)4Waveguide fabrication techniques and an introduction to the passive photonic devices5The design issues of passive photonic devices: couplers, circulators, and splitters/combiner6The design issues of passive photonic devices: MUX/DEMUX and filters7Long-period grating-based devices8Short-period grating-based devices9Midterm oral presentation10Electro-optic modulators11Magneto-optic modulators12Acousto-optic modulators13Integarted optical detectors14Optical amplifiers15Lasers: gas, solid-state, and semiconductors16Hetrostructure and distributed-feedback lasers17Device integration18Final oral presentation and final report 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


